    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Subfamily of small burrowing insectivorous mammals found throughout temperate Eurasia and North America. They usually have very poor vision, velvety fur, and short limbs with clawed toes adapted for digging the underground passages in which they live.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
